+## Handling Terminal Failures as Data
+
+Use `ctx.tryStep()` when a single step failure should become a value instead of failing the workflow:
+
+```ts
+const charge = await ctx.tryStep({
+  name: "charge-card",
+  maxRetries: 3,
+  run: async () => chargeCard(orderId),
+});
+
